nodes.title: Only Za'Dha Adamantking needs to be killed in order to win.
nodes.description: Only Za'Dha Adamantking needs to be killed in order to win. Za'Dha Adamantking is a Ranger in this mission. He stands at a distance and throws rocks if you are out of range. Za'Dha Adamantking uses Eagle Eye Shot, dealing massive damage. The lesser NMs share hate with Za'Dha Adamantking after awakening from sleep.

nodes.title: Travel to either (H-9) of Beaucedine Glacier (S), down the ramp nearby the tower where the C.A.
nodes.description: Travel to either (H-9) of Beaucedine Glacier (S), down the ramp nearby the tower where the C.A. stands when the area is under Beastmen control, or to (G-10) of Xarcabard (S) to find a ???. The area must be under Beastman control.

nodes.title: Examining the ??? will spawn a Frost Bomb, which will attack shortly after.
nodes.description: Examining the ??? will spawn a Frost Bomb, which will attack shortly after. Do not attack the snoll, but be careful to not lose all enmity and render it unclaimed.

nodes.title: Lead it to the Campaign Fortification where it will automatically use Hypothermal Combustion and dam
nodes.description: Lead it to the Campaign Fortification where it will automatically use Hypothermal Combustion and damage the fort, and only the fort. After this, the experience points will be awarded along with the message: "The stronghold has sustained considerable damage." Upon failure, the message will be: "The bombardment failed to inflict damage on the target."

nodes.title: Speak with Hieronymus to complete the Op and collect your Allied Notes.
nodes.description: Speak with Hieronymus to complete the Op and collect your Allied Notes.

nodes.title: Go to either (H-9) - at the foot of the ramp beside the C.A.'s position - of Beaucedine Glacier (S)
nodes.description: Go to either (H-9) - at the foot of the ramp beside the C.A.'s position - of Beaucedine Glacier (S) or (G-10) of Xarcabard (S) and find the ???.

nodes.title: Click the ???.
nodes.description: Click the ???. A Frost Bomb will spawn and attack immediately if you are still nearby, but will hit for fairly low damage against level 75 players. Do not attack the snoll, but be careful to not let it go unclaimed/deaggro.

nodes.title: Run to the Campaign fort with the Frost Bomb in tow.
nodes.description: Run to the Campaign fort with the Frost Bomb in tow. When you arrive, the snoll will automatically use Hypothermal Combustion and damage the fort, but it will not hurt any nearby players. You will receive the EXP award immediately. You will receive a message stating that "The stronghold has sustained considerable damage".

nodes.title: Speak with Rasdinice to complete the Op and collect your Allied Notes.
nodes.description: Speak with Rasdinice to complete the Op and collect your Allied Notes.

nodes.title: Choose either Beaucedine Glacier (S) or Xarcabard (S).
nodes.description: Choose either Beaucedine Glacier (S) or Xarcabard (S). Whichever area you choose must be beastmen-controlled.

nodes.title: Beaucedine Glacier (S): Go to (H-9), at the foot of the ramp beside the C.A.'s position and click th
nodes.description: Beaucedine Glacier (S): Go to (H-9), at the foot of the ramp beside the C.A.'s position and click the ???. Xarcabard (S): click the ??? at (G-10).

nodes.title: A Frost Bomb spawns and attacks immediately if you are still nearby, but hits for fairly low damage
nodes.description: A Frost Bomb spawns and attacks immediately if you are still nearby, but hits for fairly low damage against level 75 players. Do not attack the snoll, but be careful not to let it go unclaimed/deaggro.

nodes.title: Run to the Campaign fort with the Frost Bomb in tow.
nodes.description: Run to the Campaign fort with the Frost Bomb in tow. When you arrive, the snoll automatically uses Hypothermal Combustion to damage the fort, but it does not hurt any nearby players. You receive the EXP award immediately and a message stating that "The stronghold has sustained considerable damage".

nodes.title: In order to access the battlefield, all members must have Xicu's Rosary, which is dropped from any Y
nodes.description: In order to access the battlefield, all members must have Xicu's Rosary, which is dropped from any Yagudo in the zone (excluding notorious monsters). Drop rate is not 100%.

nodes.title: Soo Luma the Ascended (SCH) appears at the top of the arena; defeat him to win the battle.
nodes.description: Soo Luma the Ascended (SCH) appears at the top of the arena; defeat him to win the battle. Roo Beju the Eulogizer (BRD), Zjaa Bao the Wrathherald (NIN), and Jii Xai the Rimebladed (SAM) spawn to fight with Soo Luma the Ascended when he is aggroed; they do not need to be defeated to win the battle. These three respawn at the top of the arena shortly if defeated and return to fight with Soo Luma the Ascended. Pulling the Yagudo to the battlefield entrance is beneficial because the respawned helpers have a greater distance to travel before they rejoin in battle.

nodes.description: An Armoury Crate appears at the top of the arena once Soo Luma the Ascended is defeated; the remaining Yagudo despawn.

nodes.title: Accept the mission from Rasdinice.
nodes.description: Accept the mission from Rasdinice. Select Intel Gathering, then Prying Eyes.

nodes.title: Travel to La Vaule (S) and find two ???.
nodes.description: Travel to La Vaule (S) and find two ???. One is located at (K-10) at the back of a house, the other at (F-9), on what looks like a barricade archers would hide behind. Unlike Hawk Eye, the intel gathering is instantaneous, although you will still need to drop Sneak and Invisible. Both ??? are in places where you should be able to avoid aggro while clicking them.

nodes.title: Report back to Rasdinice to complete the mission.
nodes.description: Report back to Rasdinice to complete the mission.
